Source Code: https://github.com/MissBeanF/Telegram_Bot
Droplet:
1.	Clone the above url with the command “git clone https://github.com/MissBeanF/Telegram_Bot”
2.	If there is no python3 or 2 installed.
    $ sudo apt-get update
    $ sudo apt-get install python3          // this installs python 3.6 version.
3.	If there is python installed then: 
    In Telegram Bot directory run this command:
    •	If python version is 3
                     python3 main.py
    •	if python version is 2
                     python main.py
    ********************************************
    If there is an error to install requirements
        -	python –m pip install python-telegram-bot
        -	python –m pip install telepot==12.0
        -	python –m pip install requests
    After installing requirements, then try again:
         python main.py
4.	If you want to run the code in background:
          nohup python main.py &
****
  Before run this script in background, please sure that its file permission must be 755

Y ou can reference in https://janakiev.com/blog/python-background/

